recordings.loc: Wakodahatchee Wetlands, Palm Beach County, Florida
recordings.file-name: XC193124-Tricolored Heron adult called from colony and rail encoraging near full grown young from nest -FL, Wakodahatchee Wetlands, July 11, 2014, 0219 PM.mp3
recordings.rmk:
adult called from colony and boardwalk rail encoraging nearly full grown young (pair) from nest

The adult landed in colony in Pond Apple Trees but at some distance from the two nearly full-grown nestlings, encouraging them to move from the nest area.  The adult moved from the trees to the nearby boardwalk railing several times and called loudly while doing this.  The calling young birds weren't quite ready to leave the nest area.  The adult did feed them briefly.
